  "instructions": [
    "Cut the eggplant into 1-inch cubes and place them in a bowl with 2 cups of water, salt, and kombu. Let it ferment for 24 hours in the refrigerator.",
    "After fermentation, discard the kombu and water, and dry the eggplant cubes on a paper towel.",
    "Heat mustard oil in a pan and sauté the cumin seeds, onion, and tomato until they are soft.",
    "Add the fermented eggplant, red chili, garam masala, and bonito shavings to the pan and stir well.",
    "Cook for 5 minutes and serve hot with steamed rice or roti."
